The defendant David J West was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Bail Jumping-Misdemeanor, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 946.49(1)(a).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

ADA Melissa Inlow appears for the State.  Defendant appeared in person, in custody, with Attorney Sebion.  State moves to amend charge to misdemeanor bail jumping.  Court granted.  Plead guilty to the amended charge.  Court reviewed the plea questionnaire, constitutional rights and elements with the defendant.  Defendant understood. Defense stipulates to a factual basis.   Court found that the defendant freely and voluntarily entered his plea and waived his constitutional rights.  Joint recommendation for 18 months probation.  Defendant did not exercise his right to allocution.  Court ordered sentence withheld, 18 months probation.  Concurrent.    The defendant shall comply with any treatment, evaluations and/or programming as deemed appropriate by the COMPAS assessment and the probation agent.  Defendant must sign any releases agent deems necessary to verify defendant's compliance with probation conditions.  May apply for expungement, if he succesfully completes probation.  No contact with females under the age of 18 years old, unless his agent expressly allows.  CC.  Submit DNA sample.  Seek and maintain employment/school as deemed appropriate by his agent.  Credit for 52 days served.

Information will be filed later today and will have the same charges as in complaint.  Defendant waives reading of Information, stands mute.  Court enters a not guilty plea and sets pretrial and status dates.  Bond set at $1000 cash on all cases with same prior conditions with an amendment to the no contact for females under age 18.

Defendant appeared in custody in person with counsel SPD Carly Sebion.  ADA Melissa Inlow appears for the State.  State calls 1st witness, B. K, sworn, and testifies.  Witness ID's defendant and record reflects ID.  Defense questions witness.  Witness excused.  State requests court take Judicial notice of bond in this case.  State clarifies the incident took place in Clark County but was a violation of bond conditions on this case.  Defense argues there was not venue established.  Court finds there was a bond in Jackson County, venue can be either here or Clark County.  State has established an existing bond prohibiting contact with CAB.  Court binds defendant over for trial.

9:30 - Defendant appeared by video from Jackson County Jail with counsel SPD William Poss, appearing specially, present in the courtroom.  DA Gerald Fox appears for the State.  Attorney Poss states there is some confusion on what attorney is representing the defendant.  He qualifies for SPD representation but the defendant's mother possibly hired attorney Ritland.  Atty Poss states SPD Carly Sebion represents on 15CF72 & 15CF77 at this point.  He also has attorney John Matousek on other cases.  Case will be re-addressed at 1:00 with other cases on the calendar for today.  

Adjourned to 1:00 - Counsel SPD Carly Sebion present in court room.  ADA Melissa Inlow appears for the State.  Defendant appeared by VTC from Jackson County Jail.  Inlow states the defendant was to live with his brother which he never did; He was to have no contact with CAB and has; He may not show for court.  Requests a cash bond on the new case 15CF77 in addition to cash already posted.  Atty Sebion states her client is able to live with his brother and requests he be put on electronic monitoring if possible.  Court states she wants the brother present in court first as the defendant hasn't been going to school and is not following bond conditions.  Defendant states he is trying to get into Alma Center School rather than Blair-Taylor.  Attorney Sebion requests prelims be set on 15CF72 & 15CF77.  Court orders a $500 cash bond on 15CF77 with same conditions as previous bonds.  Preliminary hearings to be set on 15CF72 & 15CF77 for 1/2 hour.
